article.headline: N. Dakota St. 83, Winston-Salem 68
article.story: FARGO, N.D. (AP) -- Brett Winkelman scored 27 points and hauled down 11 rebounds to lead North Dakota State to an 83-68 victory over Winston-Salem on Wednesday. Andre Smith had 24 points and Ben Woodside 18 for the Bison (17-8). North Dakota State shot 50 percent from the field, led by Winkelman's 7 of 10 shooting, and outrebounded Winston-Salem 47-22. Winston-Salem (5-23) was led by Darrell Wonge 19 points, Norman Carter with 14 and Brian Fisher with 11. Wednesday's game was the first in a four-game home stand for NDSU.
